.TP
.B aria2.getFiles([secret], gid)
This method returns the file list of the download denoted by \fIgid\fP (string).
The response is an array of structs which contain following keys.
Values are strings.
.INDENT 7.0
.TP
.B \fBindex\fP
Index of the file, starting at 1, in the same order as files appear in the
multi\-file torrent.
.TP
.B \fBpath\fP
File path.
.TP
.B \fBlength\fP
File size in bytes.
.TP
.B \fBcompletedLength\fP
Completed length of this file in bytes.  Please note that it is
possible that sum of \fBcompletedLength\fP is less than the
\fBcompletedLength\fP returned by the \fI\%aria2.tellStatus()\fP method.
This is because \fBcompletedLength\fP in
\fI\%aria2.getFiles()\fP
only includes completed pieces. On the other hand, \fBcompletedLength\fP
in \fI\%aria2.tellStatus()\fP also includes partially completed pieces.
.TP
.B \fBselected\fP
\fBtrue\fP if this file is selected by \fI\%\-\-select\-file\fP option. If
\fI\%\-\-select\-file\fP is not specified or this is single\-file torrent or
not a torrent download at all, this value is always \fBtrue\fP\&. Otherwise
\fBfalse\fP\&.
.TP
.B \fBuris\fP
Returns a list of URIs for this file. The element type is the same struct
used in the \fI\%aria2.getUris()\fP method.
.UNINDENT
.sp
\fBJSON\-RPC Example\fP
.INDENT 7.0
.INDENT 3.5
.sp
